69",{"_":172,"when":173,"who":157},"Jonathan Prag made initial revision from publication","2025-11-03",[],[176,177,178,179],"Notizie degli scavi di antichità, 1876-","Pace, 1949, Arte e civiltà della Sicilia antica. Volume quarto. Barbari e Bizantini","Soraci, 1958, Appunti di epigrafia greca e romana relativa alla regione hyblense-inessea-adranita","Ferrua, 1989, Note e giunte alle iscrizioni cristiane antiche della Sicilia",[181,182,183,184],"4MCP2PVV","ZEDFITDZ","ZXGG3V8Z","759ZXHKQ",[186,187,188,26,31,35,189,190,191,192,193,194,195,109],"isic002993","dedication of church entrance",{"_":5},"hybla gereatis","paternò","sicilia","sicily","paterno","chiesa dell'annunziata","ancient greek",[],{"title":198,"body":199,"divs":200,"editions":225,"images":235,"handnote":236},"ISic002993. Dedication of church entrance","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>θ(εο)\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ῦ\u003C/span> οἴκ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">ο&lt;͡υ&gt;\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>εἴσ\u003Cspan class=\"error\" title=\"hi tag with rend=stacked is not supported!\">ο\u003C/span>οδο \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Θ\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">Υ\u003C/span>ΟΙΚ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Ο\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΕΙΣ\u003Cspan class=\"error\" title=\"hi tag with rend=stacked is not supported!\">Ο\u003C/span>ΟΔΟ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text after Orsi 1903 with suggestions of Ferrua 1989\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Ferrua suggests that omicron at the end of line 1 was originally the ligatured form ȣ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Ferrua suggests that the lower of the two stacked omicrons in line 2 might be lunate sigma for the end of εἴσοδος (in which case actually line 3)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Entrance of the house of God\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Orsi declined to resolve the text, which he thought Archaic. Subsequent editions by Pace, Soraci, and Ferrua are all derivative of Orsi's drawing. Pace first proposed the Christian resolution, which would seem to be from above the entrance to a church.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1903 441 dr \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Pace 1949 196 dr \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001690\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001690\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Soraci 1958 253 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001571\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001571\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1989 no.470 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Described by Orsi as archaic Greek letters, but seems more likely a Christian text, crudely cut on coarse stone.\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[201,204,207,210,213,216,219,222],{"id":202,"html":203},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>θ(εο)\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ῦ\u003C/span> οἴκ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">ο&lt;͡υ&gt;\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>εἴσ\u003Cspan class=\"error\" title=\"hi tag with rend=stacked is not supported!\">ο\u003C/span>οδο \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u00