rua are all derivative of Orsi's drawing. Pace first proposed the Christian resolution, which would seem to be from above the entrance to a church.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":217,"html":218},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1903 441 dr \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Pace 1949 196 dr \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001690\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001690\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Soraci 1958 253 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001571\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001571\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1989 no.470 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":220,"html":221},"handnote","\u003Cp>Described by Orsi as archaic Greek letters, but seems more likely a Christian text, crudely cut on coarse stone.\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":223,"html":224},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[226,228,231,232],{"html":227},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV\u003C/a>",{"id":229,"lang":109,"html":230},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>θ(εο)\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ῦ\u003C/span> οἴκ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">ο&lt;͡υ&gt;\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u00